{"id": "EUVD-2022-55171", "enisaUuid": "64095dc8-fc68-321d-858f-79e7914c8a8b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndevice property: fix of node refcount leak in fwnode_graph_get_next_endpoint()\n\nThe 'parent' returned by fwnode_graph_get_port_parent()\nwith refcount incremented when 'prev' is not NULL, it\nneeds be put when finish using it.\n\nBecause the parent is const, introduce a new variable to\nstore the returned fwnode, then put it before returning\nfrom fwnode_graph_get_next_endpoint().", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T16:43:00", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:26:35", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7701a4bd45c11f9a289d8f262fad05705a012339", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e75485fc589ec729cc182aa9b41dfb6c15ae6f6e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/39af728649b05e88a2b40e714feeee6451c3f18e"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49752"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "30591684-2792-397a-b217-573213d6ff31", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "6b4ce287-1217-3d6b-922b-21a8265c8cb1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5b41ab6b0c1bb70fe37a0d193006c969e3b5909 <e75485fc589ec729cc182aa9b41dfb6c15ae6f6e"}, {"id": "7b310081-49b9-3311-adbf-1a34ddfff367", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5b41ab6b0c1bb70fe37a0d193006c969e3b5909 <39af728649b05e88a2b40e714feeee6451c3f18e"}, {"id": "7db63c16-63e5-3edd-bb18-3c8bb0707cf5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5b41ab6b0c1bb70fe37a0d193006c969e3b5909 <7701a4bd45c11f9a289d8f262fad05705a012339"}, {"id": "aa9f185b-662c-376c-8a1e-0a3a857818ce", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "c3d6044f-2fc4-3c6c-a001-a03e7991d116", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.9"}, {"id": "f46b82c9-82ca-3afc-b81c-e7dc139a0094", "pro